=Discussion=

Strongly recommended by Michel Bauwens:

John Hamer is a pastor in a offshoot of Mormonism that evolved somewhat like the Unitarian Universalists, but what he offers here is historically grounded and can be of benefit to everyone who is interested in the history of religion and spirituality. It includes the occasional foray in political themes, such as a history of the Venetian Republic, which lasted nearly a thousand years. If you are interested in understanding the religious background of our human civilizations and undertake some form of self-study based on shared resources you can find through the internet, look no further.

